><div style=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;Inter&#39;,&#39=
;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;line-height:1=
50%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margi=
n-bottom:0px;">Earlier this week, before heading to New Orleans for the Sup=
er Bowl, Fox Corp.
chairman and C.E.O. <strong>Lachlan Murdoch </strong>kicked off the company=
=E2=80=99s earnings call by touting a record $781 million in EBITDA for the=
 quarter, fueled by 20 percent growth in advertising revenue=E2=80=94a surg=
e that Murdoch attributed to the presidential election and live sports. The=
 future looked similarly bright: Fox had long ago sold out its inventory fo=
r Sunday=E2=80=99s Chiefs-Eagles game =E2=80=9Cwith record pricing,=E2=80=
=9D capping a postseason in which it had enjoyed its highest-ever pricing a=
nd demand for NFL
games. None of this was surprising, of course; ever since <strong>Rupert </=
strong>sold his entertainment empire to Disney, Fox has practically become =
a live-programming pure play=E2=80=94and the strategy=E2=80=99s success has=
 been evident from the company=E2=80=99s performance.</p><p style=3D"margin=
:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">W=
hat Lachlan said next was even more remarkable, though: Since the election =
in November, Fox News had seen =E2=80=9Cincreased demand from existing blue
chip advertisers as well as new clients coming to the network due to its re=
cord share of audience,=E2=80=9D which now comprises <em>70 percent</em> of=
 cable news viewership. Asked to elaborate, Lachlan specified that Fox News=
 had, since the election, added =E2=80=9Cover 100 new clients who have not =
been Fox News advertisers=E2=80=9D and that he expected more inbound as the=
 cable network=E2=80=99s ratings and revenue increased in the next quarter.=
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0=
;
margin-bottom:0px;">Fox Corp.=E2=80=99s ad sales chief, <strong>Jeff Collin=
s</strong>, later told me the number of new clients actually exceeded 120. =
He declined to name any of them, oddly, though <em>The Five</em>=E2=80=99s =
Friday broadcast included creative from Amazon, General Motors, and Unileve=
r. (Collins also said that the vast majority of these new clients had <em>n=
ot </em>come in as part of Super Bowl=E2=80=93related deals.)</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bott=
om:
0px;">Yes, <em>advertisers follow audience </em>in this business, but Fox N=
ews=E2=80=99s unique place in the ecosystem has long complicated that relat=
ionship. Fox has bested its cable competitors in the ratings <em>for years<=
/em>, historically doubling MSNBC=E2=80=99s audience and quadrupling CNN=E2=
=80=99s increasingly meager haul. By its own account, it has been the top n=
etwork in basic cable for the last eight years and the most watched televis=
ion news channel for the last 22. Nevertheless, it has long struggled to
attract big advertisers, and for all the obvious reasons: The audience for =
cable news is <em>old</em>, averaging around 70 years of age, and the vast =
majority of blue chip advertisers have long been averse to marketing alongs=
ide news content, particularly political content=E2=80=94and <em>particular=
ly</em> the sort of highly partisan and occasionally batshit crazy stuff th=
at leads to $787 million defamation settlements. At least, that is, until n=
ow.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">The influx of such cli=
ents is, therefore, quite notable=E2=80=94not just as a business developmen=
t, but as the sign of a political and cultural shift. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s=
 a big fucking deal,=E2=80=9D veteran media analyst <strong>Rich Greenfield=
</strong> told me. Historically, Fox News =E2=80=9Cwas, like, ads for gold;=
 I couldn=E2=80=99t name a network with worse advertising partners,=E2=80=
=9D he said. =E2=80=9CNow, blue chip advertisers like Unilever have come ba=
ck onto the platform.=E2=80=9D</p></div>
